## Chapter 5: Layer L – Linguistic Authenticity

### 5.1 Topic Embedding & Clustering
Posts $\{x_j\}$ are embedded via DistilBERT into $\mathbf{h}_j \in \mathbb{R}^d$. Spherical $k$-means clusters into $K$ topics. Empirical distribution for account $a$:
$$
\hat{P}_a(k) = \frac{1}{|A_a|} \sum_{x \in A_a} \mathbb{I}(\text{cluster}(x) = k)
$$

### 5.2 Stratified Divergence & Loss
Global human baseline $P_{\text{human}}$ is stratified by language, domain, and account age to avoid penalizing niche experts. We use symmetric Jensen-Shannon divergence:
$$
\mathcal{L}_L = 1 - \exp\left(- \frac{D_{JS}(P_{\text{strat}} \| \hat{P}_a)}{\log K}\right)
$$
High entropy $\mathcal{S}(a) \approx \log K - 0.5$ indicates semantic diversity. Narrow LLM fine-tuning collapses $\mathcal{S}(a)$, increasing $\mathcal{L}_L$.

### 5.3 Cold-Start & Activity Threshold
$\mathcal{L}_L$ is only computed when $|A_a| \geq 50$. Below threshold, prior $\mathcal{L}_L \sim \text{Uniform}(0.3, 0.5)$ with variance decaying as $|A_a|^{-1/2}$.

