## Chapter 7: Layer C – Collective Synchronicity & Null-Model Testing

### 7.1 Activity Tensor & Cross-Correlation
For cluster $A = \{a_1,\dots,a_m\}$, define binary activity $X_i(t)$. Cross-correlation at lag $\tau$:
$$
\mathcal{X}_{ij}(\tau) = \frac{\sum_t X_i(t)X_j(t+\tau)}{\sqrt{\sum_t X_i(t)^2 \sum_t X_j(t)^2}}
$$

### 7.2 Synchronicity Metric
$$
\Psi(A) = \frac{1}{m(m-1)} \sum_{i \neq j} \max_{\tau \in [-\delta, +\delta]} \mathcal{X}_{ij}(\tau), \quad \delta = 10\text{s}
$$

### 7.3 Surrogate Null-Model Testing
Viral events induce global spikes. To isolate coordinated phase-locking, we generate $K=1000$ null distributions by time-shifting each account’s timeline by $\delta_i \sim \text{Uniform}(-1\text{h}, +1\text{h})$, preserving marginal rates but destroying coordination.
$$
Z_\Psi = \frac{\Psi_{\text{obs}} - \mu_{\text{null}}}{\sigma_{\text{null}}}
$$
If $Z_\Psi > 3$, synchronicity is statistically significant ($p < 0.001$).

### 7.4 Synchronicity Loss
$$
\mathcal{L}_C(A) = \min\left(1, \frac{\Psi(A)}{0.3} \cdot \mathbb{I}(Z_\Psi > 3)\right)
$$
Accounts in phase-locked clusters receive multiplicative penalty: $H(a) \leftarrow H(a)(1 - \mathcal{L}_C)$.

