## Chapter 8: Probabilistic Inference & Calibration

### 8.1 Bayesian Logistic Regression
$$
P(\text{Human} \mid \mathcal{L}) = \frac{1}{1 + e^{-(\beta_0 + \boldsymbol{\beta}^\top \mathcal{L})}}, \quad \boldsymbol{\beta} \sim \mathcal{N}(0, \sigma^2 I)
$$
Updated weekly via online variational inference. Gold standard: verified identities + historically confirmed botnet takedowns.

### 8.2 Temperature Scaling
To correct overconfidence, apply temperature $T$:
$$
H_{\text{cal}}(a) = \sigma\left(\frac{1}{T} \log \frac{H(a)}{1-H(a)}\right)
$$
$T$ optimized via NLL on validation set. Ensures $H_{\text{cal}}$ is a true probability.

### 8.3 SHAP Attribution & Counterfactuals
Shapley values: $\phi_i = \sum_{S \subseteq \mathcal{L}\setminus\{i\}} \frac{|S|!(3-|S|)!}{4!} [f(S\cup\{i\}) - f(S)]$.  
UI displays: “Low $H$ because network is low-conductance ($\phi_N=0.48$). Increase external interaction diversity to raise score.”

### 8.4 Cold-Start Priors
For $|A_a| < 50$: $H_{\text{prior}} \sim \text{Beta}(2,1)$. Posterior smoothed until layer signals stabilize.

